## 1. Technology Stack

### 1.1 Core Stack

| Layer | Choice | Rationale |
|-------|--------|-----------|
| Language | C++17 (C++20 preferred) | Qt ecosystem; performance-critical rendering and VT processing |
| UI Framework | Qt 6 (≥ 6.5) — Quick, Core, Gui | Chi library requirement; QML for declarative UI chrome |
| UI Components | Chi 1.0 | Material 3 Expressive; theme-driven; zero-config beauty |
| VT Emulation | libghostty-vt (primary) / libvterm (fallback) | See §4 for detailed rationale |
| Config Format | TOML via toml++ | Human-readable, typed, version-control friendly |
| Build | CMake ≥ 3.19 | Industry standard, FetchContent for dependency management |
| Compiler | GCC 13+ / Clang 16+ | C++17 minimum, sanitizer support |

### 1.2 Why These Libraries

**VT Emulation — libghostty-vt (primary):**
- Extracted from Ghostty's terminal emulator core
- SIMD-optimized VT sequence parsing
- Leading Unicode support (full grapheme clustering)
- Zero external dependencies
- Fuzz-tested, proven by millions of daily users
- C API under active development; dozens of projects already integrating
- Handles: Kitty Keyboard Protocol, Kitty Graphics Protocol parsing,
  synchronized rendering, text reflow, scrollback management

**VT Emulation — libvterm (fallback):**
- Abstract C99 library implementing VT220/xterm
- No graphics toolkit dependency — pure callback-based
- Avoids malloc() during normal operation
- Used by Neovim's built-in terminal — well-proven
- Our safety net if libghostty's C API timeline slips
- Both libraries use callback architectures → our bridge adapts cleanly

**Why NOT these alternatives:**

| Library | Rejection Reason |
|---------|-----------------|
| QTermWidget | GPL-licensed, Qt Widgets-based (not QML), heavy Konsole heritage |
| VTE (GNOME) | GTK-specific, cannot embed in Qt |
| xterm.js | JavaScript/browser — wrong platform entirely |
| yat / literm | Unmaintained, limited VT emulation |
| Writing our own | VT emulation is deceptively complex; 12+ months of edge cases |

**Config — toml++:**
- Header-only C++17, MIT license
- Full TOML v1.0 compliance
- Supports serialization (read and write)
- Exception-free mode available
- Tiny footprint, no dependencies

### 1.3 System Dependencies (Linux)

**Build time:**
- Qt 6.5+ (Core, Gui, Quick, QuickControls2, DBus, Network, ShaderTools)
- CMake ≥ 3.19, Ninja (recommended)
- GCC 13+ or Clang 16+
- Zig 0.15.x (only if building libghostty-vt from source)

**Runtime:**
- Mesa / libGL (for Qt Quick Scene Graph GPU backend)
- fontconfig, FreeType, HarfBuzz (via Qt)
- D-Bus (for desktop integration)

---

## 2. System Layers
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │ QML UI Layer │ │ Chi components: TabBar, ContextMenu, SearchOverlay, │ │ StatusBar, CommandPalette, SideSheet, Dialog, Settings │ ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤ │ TerminalWidget Layer │ │ Custom QQuickItem — renders terminal grid via Scene Graph │ │ Glyph atlas, selection overlay, cursor, link underlines │ ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤ │ Session Management Layer │ │ SessionManager, TerminalSession, SplitTree │ │ Coordinates tabs, panes, focus, lifecycle │ ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤ │ Terminal Engine Layer │ │ VtBridge (abstraction) → libghostty-vt or libvterm │ │ ScreenBuffer (cell grid + scrollback ring buffer) │ │ Selection model, SearchEngine │ ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤ │ PTY Layer │ │ PtyManager: forkpty(), QSocketNotifier, read/write, resize │ ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤ │ Configuration Layer │ │ ConfigManager (TOML), KeybindingManager, ColorScheme │ │ ShellIntegration (OSC parsing), ContextDetector │ ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤ │ Platform Layer │ │ DesktopIntegration (D-Bus notifications, global shortcuts) │ │ WaylandHelpers, X11Helpers │ └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

text


**Data flow for a keypress:**
User presses key → QML KeyEvent → KeybindingManager checks for terminal action → If bound: execute action (new tab, split, etc.) → If not bound: encode for terminal → VtBridge.encodeKey() → byte sequence → PtyManager.write() → master FD → Shell process reads from slave FD

text


**Data flow for terminal output:**
Shell writes to slave FD → Kernel PTY layer → PtyManager reads from master FD (QSocketNotifier) → VtBridge.feed(data) → parse VT sequences → ScreenBuffer updated, dirty flags set → TerminalWidget.update() triggered → Scene Graph node tree rebuilt for dirty cells → GPU renders frame

text


---

## 3. Module Map
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │ chi-terminal │ │ │ │ ┌──────────┐ ┌──────────┐ ┌──────────────────┐ │ │ │ terminal/ │ │rendering/│ │ session/ │ │ │ │ │ │ │ │ │ │ │ │ PtyMgr │←→│TermWidget│←→│ SessionManager │ │ │ │ VtBridge │ │ GlyphAtl │ │ TerminalSession │ │ │ │ ScreenBuf │ │ TermNode │ │ SplitNode │ │ │ │ Selection │ │ CursorRen│ │ Persistence (T2) │ │ │ │ Search │ │ │ │ │ │ │ └──────────┘ └──────────┘ └──────────────────┘ │ │ ↑ ↑ ↑ │ │ │ │ │ │ │ ┌──────────┐ ┌──────────┐ ┌──────────────────┐ │ │ │ config/ │ │ context/ │ │ platform/ │ │ │ │ │ │ │ │ │ │ │ │ ConfigMgr │ │ Detector │ │ DesktopInteg │ │ │ │ Keybinds │ │ MenuBuild│ │ GlobalShortcut │ │ │ │ ColorSchm │ │ │ │ WaylandHelpers │ │ │ │ ShellIntg │ │ │ │ │ │ │ └──────────┘ └──────────┘ └──────────────────┘ │ │ │ │ ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │ │ │ qml/ (UI Layer) │ │ │ │ Main.qml, TabBar, Pane, SplitView, Search, │ │ │ │ ContextMenu, StatusBar, CommandPalette (T2), │ │ │ │ Settings (T2), AiPanel (T3) │ │ │ └──────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

text


**Module dependency rules:**
- `terminal/` depends on nothing in the project (standalone)
- `rendering/` depends on `terminal/` (reads ScreenBuffer)
- `session/` depends on `terminal/` and `rendering/`
- `config/` depends on nothing (standalone, consumed by others)
- `context/` depends on `terminal/` (reads screen content)
- `platform/` depends on nothing in the project (standalone)
- `qml/` depends on everything (top of the stack)

No circular dependencies. Each module is independently testable.

---

## 4. Terminal Emulation Layer

### 4.1 VtBridge — Backend Abstraction

The VtBridge provides a uniform interface over whichever VT library
is active. This is the core abstraction that lets us swap backends.

**Responsibilities:**
- Accept raw bytes from PTY → parse VT sequences → update screen state
- Provide cell-by-cell access to the terminal grid
- Track cursor position, style, visibility
- Manage scrollback ring buffer
- Encode keyboard input and mouse events into VT sequences
- Emit signals for: screen damage, bell, title changes, hyperlinks,
  clipboard requests (OSC 52), color queries

**Backend selection:**
- Compile-time flag: `CHITERM_USE_GHOSTTY` or `CHITERM_USE_LIBVTERM`
- Both backends implement the same VtBridge interface
- Backend can be switched without touching any other module

### 4.2 ScreenBuffer

**Responsibilities:**
- Store the active terminal grid (rows × cols of Cells)
- Store the scrollback buffer as a ring buffer of rows
- Track dirty regions (which cells changed since last render)
- Handle text reflow when terminal resizes

**Design decisions:**
- Ring buffer for scrollback (constant-time append, bounded memory)
- Dirty tracking via per-row bitflags (not per-cell — cache-friendly)
- Double-buffered: VT engine writes to back buffer, renderer reads
  from front buffer, swap on "



  
  
  
   
   
 
 
 
  
  
  
  

" (not "per byte")

### 4.3 Selection Model

**Responsibilities:**
- Track selection start/end in grid coordinates
- Support: linear (normal), word, line, rectangular modes
- Convert selection to plain text for clipboard
- Handle selection across scrollback boundary
- Invalidate selection when underlying content scrolls

### 4.4 Search Engine

**Responsibilities:**
- Search through ScreenBuffer (visible + scrollback)
- Support plain text and PCRE2 regex (via QRegularExpression)
- Return match positions as grid coordinates
- Track "current match" index for navigation
- Incremental search (update results as user types)

---

## 5. PTY Management

### 5.1 PtyManager

**Responsibilities:**
- Create pseudoterminal pair via `forkpty()`
- Spawn child process (user's shell) on the slave side
- Async read from master FD via `QSocketNotifier`
- Write to master FD (user input, encoded by VtBridge)
- Handle terminal resize via `TIOCSWINSZ` ioctl
- Detect child exit via `SIGCHLD` / `waitpid()`
- Report foreground process name via `tcgetpgrp()` + `/proc`

**Design decisions:**
- One PtyManager per TerminalSession (1:1)
- Read in chunks (buffer to be sized during implementation)
- Write coalescing: buffer small writes, flush per event loop tick
- Environment: inherit parent env + set `TERM`, `COLORTERM`,
  `CHITERM_VERSION`, shell integration vars

### 5.2 Signal Handling

- `SIGCHLD`: detected via Qt signal handler or `signalfd()`
- `SIGWINCH`: not needed (we control resize via ioctl, not signals)
- `SIGTERM`/`SIGINT`: graceful shutdown, save session state (Tier 2)

---

## 6. Rendering Pipeline

### 6.1 Strategy: Custom QQuickItem + Scene Graph

The terminal grid is rendered as a **custom QQuickItem** that builds
a Qt Scene Graph node tree directly. This is critical for performance.

**Why NOT QML Text elements:**
- A 200×50 terminal = 10,000 cells = 10,000 QObjects if using Text {}
- QObject overhead: ~160 bytes each + property system + signal/slot
- Scene Graph nodes: ~64 bytes each, no QObject overhead
- Direct Scene Graph is 10-50x more efficient for a character grid

**Why NOT raw OpenGL/Vulkan:**
- Qt Scene Graph already uses RHI (Rendering Hardware Interface)
- RHI abstracts OpenGL, Vulkan, Metal, Direct3D
- We get GPU acceleration without platform-specific graphics code
- Integrates correctly with QML compositing (overlays, popups, etc.)

### 6.2 Glyph Atlas

A single large texture containing pre-rendered glyphs.

**Strategy:**
- On font change: pre-render ASCII printable range (32-126) into atlas
- On demand: render and cache additional glyphs as encountered
- Hash map: codepoint + style flags → atlas coordinates
- Atlas growth: start at a reasonable size, grow if needed
- Emoji: rendered via separate color glyph path (system emoji font)

**Each cell is rendered as:**
1. Background quad (solid color from cell.bg)
2. Foreground textured quad (glyph from atlas, tinted by cell.fg)
3. Optional: underline/strikethrough geometry
4. Optional: cursor overlay

### 6.3 Dirty Rendering

Only re-render what changed:
- VT engine marks dirty rows via ScreenBuffer flags
- On `updatePaintNode()`, iterate only dirty rows
- Update corresponding QSGNode children
- Clear dirty flags after render
- Result: typical interactive use re-renders 1-3 rows per frame

### 6.4 Cursor Rendering

- Block: filled rectangle (or outlined when unfocused)
- Beam: thin vertical line (1-2px)
- Underline: horizontal line at cell bottom
- Blink: QML Timer-driven opacity animation (Chi motion tokens)

### 6.5 Selection Rendering

- Semi-transparent overlay rectangles on selected cells
- Color from ChiTheme: primaryContainer at reduced opacity
- Updated per-frame if selection is being dragged

---

## 7. Session & Layout Model

### 7.1 Hierarchy
Application └─ Window (may have multiple in future) └─ TabModel (ordered list of tabs) └─ Tab └─ SplitTree (root SplitNode) ├─ SplitNode (type: leaf) → TerminalSession └─ SplitNode (type: hsplit or vsplit) ├─ first → SplitNode └─ second → SplitNode

text


### 7.2 SplitTree

A binary tree where:
- **Leaf nodes** contain a TerminalSession
- **Branch nodes** define a horizontal or vertical split with a ratio

**Operations:**
- `split(node, direction)` → replace leaf with branch + 2 leaves
- `close(node)` → remove leaf, replace parent branch with sibling
- `maximize(node)` → temporarily render only this leaf (zen mode)
- `navigate(direction)` → find adjacent leaf in the tree
- `resize(node, delta)` → adjust parent branch ratio

**Layout pass:**
- Given the root node's bounding rectangle
- Recursively subdivide: branch nodes divide by ratio and direction
- Leaf nodes receive their final QRectF → TerminalWidget sizes to fit

### 7.3 TerminalSession

One TerminalSession represents one running terminal instance.
It owns:
- One PtyManager (subprocess)
- One VtBridge (VT emulation)
- One ScreenBuffer (cell grid + scrollback)
- One SelectionModel
- Shell integration state (CWD, last exit code, timing)

### 7.4 SessionManager

Singleton that manages the application-level session:
- Tab list (ordered)
- Active tab / active pane tracking
- Tab create / close / reorder
- Focus routing
- Session persistence (Tier 2): serialize → JSON, restore on launch

---

## 8. Configuration System

### 8.1 ConfigManager

**Responsibilities:**
- Load TOML from XDG-compliant path
- Parse and validate against schema (known keys + types)
- Provide typed getters with defaults for missing keys
- Watch file for changes via QFileSystemWatcher
- On change: re-parse, compute delta, emit change signals

**Hot-reloadable (no restart):**
Colors, fonts, opacity, cursor style, keybindings, padding,
tab bar visibility, status bar visibility, bell settings

**Requires restart:**
Shell, TERM value, GPU rendering mode

### 8.2 KeybindingManager

**Responsibilities:**
- Parse keybinding config into internal representation
- Match incoming QKeyEvent against registered bindings
- Support multi-key sequences (future)
- Detect conflicts (two actions bound to same key)
- Provide list of all actions + current bindings (for settings GUI)

### 8.3 ColorScheme

**Responsibilities:**
- Load color scheme files (TOML native format)
- Import foreign formats: iTerm2 (.itermcolors XML), Xresources
- Map ANSI 16 colors + extended colors
- Integration with ChiTheme: terminal chrome uses theme tokens,
  terminal content uses scheme colors

---

## 9. Shell Integration

### 9.1 OSC Sequence Handling

Shell integration scripts (shipped for bash, zsh, fish) emit OSC
sequences that the VT engine forwards to ShellIntegration handler:

| Sequence | Data | Use |
|----------|------|-----|
| OSC 7 | `file://hostname/path` | CWD tracking |
| OSC 133;A | — | Prompt start |
| OSC 133;B | — | Command start |
| OSC 133;C | — | Output start |
| OSC 133;D;N | exit code N | Command finished |
| OSC 0 / 1 / 2 | title string | Window/icon title |

### 9.2 Derived State

From these sequences, ShellIntegration computes:
- Current working directory
- Whether shell is at a prompt vs. running a command
- Command start/end boundaries (for block-based output in Tier 2)
- Command duration (time between OSC 133;B and 133;D)
- Last exit code

---

## 10. Context Detection System

### 10.1 ContextDetector

Analyzes text at a given position in the terminal grid to determine
what semantic element is under the cursor.

**Detection strategies (priority order):**
1. OSC 8 hyperlinks (explicit, highest confidence)
2. URL regex (http://, https://, ftp://, etc.)
3. File path patterns (/, ~/, ./, ../  + existence check)
4. IP address patterns (IPv4, IPv6)
5. Email patterns
6. If text is selected → "selected text" context
7. Otherwise → "empty" context

### 10.2 ContextMenuBuilder

Takes a Context enum + detected text → produces a list of menu items
appropriate for that context. Consumed by the QML ContextMenu.

---

## 11. UI Layer (QML + Chi)

### 11.1 Component Mapping

| UI Element | Chi Component(s) | Notes |
|-----------|-------------------|-------|
| Tab bar | Custom (thin bar) + IconButton | Compact, ≤36px |
| Tab | Custom delegate | Drag-reorderable |
| Context menu | ContextMenu + MenuItem + MenuDivider | Dynamic per context |
| Search overlay | Card + TextField + IconButton + ToggleButton | Floating, top-right |
| Status bar | Custom bar + IconLabel + Icon | Compact, ≤24px |
| Command palette (T2) | Dialog + SearchBar + ListView + ListItem | Modal, top-center |
| Settings panel (T2) | SideSheet + Tabs + form components | Right-side panel |
| AI panel (T3) | SideSheet + Card + TextField + Button | Right-side panel |
| Confirmations | ConfirmDialog | Tab close, etc. |
| Notifications | Snackbar | Command completed, etc. |

### 11.2 Layout Strategy
┌─ Window ────────────────────────────────────┐ │ ┌─ TabBar ─────────────────────────────────┐│ │ │ [≡] [Tab 1] [Tab 2] [Tab 3] [+] ││ │ └──────────────────────────────────────────┘│ │ ┌─ Content Area ───────────────────────────┐│ │ │ ││ │ │ SplitView (recursive) ││ │ │ └─ TerminalPane(s) ││ │ │ └─ TerminalWidget (QQuickItem) ││ │ │ ││ │ └──────────────────────────────────────────┘│ │ ┌─ StatusBar ──────────────────────────────┐│ │ │ 📁 ~/projects/chi-terminal ⎇ main ⏱ 2.3s ✓││ │ └──────────────────────────────────────────┘│ └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘

text


**No TopAppBar**: Terminal maximizes screen real estate. The tab bar
serves as the top chrome. Menu access via hamburger button in tab bar.

### 11.3 Overlay Strategy

Overlays (search, command palette) float above terminal content using
QML z-ordering. They do NOT take space from the terminal grid. They
are dismissed on Escape or click-outside.

---

## 12. AI Subsystem (Tier 3)

### 12.1 Backend Architecture

AI backends are plugins behind a common interface:
AiPanel (QML) ↕ signals/slots AiManager (C++) ↕ selects active backend AiBackend (abstract) ├─ OllamaBackend → HTTP to localhost:11434 ├─ OpenAiBackend → HTTPS to api.openai.com └─ AnthropicBackend → HTTPS to api.anthropic.com

text


**All backends support:**
- Streaming responses (token-by-token display)
- Cancellation mid-response
- System prompt with terminal context (opt-in)

**Networking:** Qt Network (`QNetworkAccessManager`) for HTTP/HTTPS.
No additional HTTP library needed.

**Secret storage:** API keys stored via system keyring (libsecret
on Linux, accessed via D-Bus). Never stored in plaintext config.

### 12.2 Context Passing

When the user asks AI for help, they can optionally include terminal
context. The UI must show exactly what text will be sent before
transmission. Context options:
- Last command + output (current block)
- Selected text only
- Last N lines
- None (just the user's question)

---

## 13. Platform Integration

### 13.1 D-Bus Services Used

| Service | Use | Tier |
|---------|-----|------|
| `org.freedesktop.Notifications` | Desktop notifications | T2 |
| `org.freedesktop.portal.GlobalShortcuts` | Quake-mode hotkey | T2 |
| `org.freedesktop.secrets` | API key storage | T3 |

### 13.2 Wayland Considerations

- Use Qt's Wayland backend (automatic with `QT_QPA_PLATFORM=wayland`)
- Layer shell for quake-mode (via `wlr-layer-shell` or portal)
- No X11-specific code in core; platform/ module isolates differences

### 13.3 XDG Compliance

| Spec | Path | Use |
|------|------|-----|
| `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME` | `~/.config/chiterm/` | Config files |
| `$XDG_DATA_HOME` | `~/.local/share/chiterm/` | Color schemes, shell integration scripts |
| `$XDG_STATE_HOME` | `~/.local/state/chiterm/` | Session persistence, history |
| `$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR` | `/run/user/$UID/chiterm/` | Socket for single-instance |

