## 16. Testing Architecture

### 16.1 Unit Tests (Qt Test)

| Module | Test Focus |
|--------|------------|
| terminal/PtyManager | Spawn, read/write, resize, exit detection |
| terminal/VtBridge | Feed sequences → verify cell state |
| terminal/ScreenBuffer | Write, scroll, reflow, dirty tracking |
| terminal/Selection | Word/line/rect selection, coordinate math |
| terminal/SearchEngine | Plain text, regex, case, match navigation |
| config/ConfigManager | Valid/invalid TOML, defaults, hot reload |
| config/KeybindingManager | Parse, match, conflict detection |
| config/ColorScheme | Load native, import iTerm2/Xresources |
| context/ContextDetector | URL, path, IP, email regex accuracy |

### 16.2 Integration Tests

| Test | What It Validates |
|------|-------------------|
| vttest suite | VT220/xterm escape sequence compliance |
| True color test | 24-bit color rendering accuracy |
| Unicode test suite | Grapheme clusters, wide chars, combining |
| tmux compatibility | Nested multiplexer works fully |
| Neovim compatibility | Kitty Keyboard Protocol, cursor shapes |
| lazygit / btop / htop | TUI rendering correctness |

### 16.3 Performance Tests

| Test | What It Measures |
|------|-----------------|
| Throughput | Bytes/sec: `cat` large file |
| Latency | Keypress → pixel change (ms) |
| Scrollback nav | FPS while scrolling 100K lines |
| Startup | Time to first rendered frame |
| Reflow | Time to resize during heavy output |

### 16.4 CI Pipeline

- **Build matrix**: GCC 13 + Clang 16, Qt 6.5 + Qt 6.7
- **Unit tests**: All, with ASan + UBSan
- **Integration**: vttest, TUI app smoke tests
- **Performance**: Track across commits, alert on regression
- **Lint**: clang-tidy, QML linter

