4.11 Configuration System
4.11.1 Config File Location
Following XDG Base Directory specification:

text

$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/chiterm/chiterm.toml
  → typically ~/.config/chiterm/chiterm.toml
4.11.2 Config Schema
toml

# chiterm.toml — full Tier 1 config

[general]
shell = ""                    # empty = $SHELL or /bin/sh
initial_directory = ""        # empty = $HOME
term = "xterm-256color"       # TERM environment variable
scrollback_lines = 10000      # 0 = disabled, -1 = unlimited
confirm_close = true          # prompt if process is running
close_on_exit = true          # close pane when shell exits
audible_bell = false
visual_bell = true

[font]
family = "monospace"          # CSS-style font-family
size = 13
bold_family = ""              # empty = auto
italic_family = ""            # empty = auto
ligatures = true
line_height = 1.0             # multiplier

[appearance]
theme = "auto"                # auto | light | dark
color_scheme = "material"     # material | catppuccin | tokyo-night | ...
opacity = 1.0                 # 0.0 - 1.0 (requires compositor)
blur = false                  # background blur (Wayland only)
cursor_style = "block"        # block | beam | underline
cursor_blink = true
cursor_blink_interval = 500   # ms
padding = 8                   # terminal content padding in px

[tabs]
show_tab_bar = "multiple"     # always | multiple | never
tab_position = "top"          # top
new_tab_position = "end"      # end | after_current
show_close_button = true

[keybindings]
# ... as above, all overridable

[advanced]
gpu_rendering = true
force_wayland = false
force_x11 = false
4.11.3 Live Reload
Watch config file via QFileSystemWatcher
On change: re-parse, validate, apply delta
Hot-reloadable: colors, fonts, opacity, keybindings, most UI settings
Requires restart: shell, TERM, GPU rendering mode
4.12 Shell Integration
4.12.1 Requirements
Feature	Detail	Priority
CWD tracking	Know current directory per pane	P0
Command timing	Duration of last command	P0
Exit code indicator	✓ green / ✗ red in status bar	P0
Process detection	Detect foreground process name	P0
Auto title	Tab title from CWD + command	P0
4.12.2 Implementation
Shell integration via standard OSC sequences:

OSC 7 (CWD): \e]7;file://hostname/path\a
OSC 133 (command prompts): Semantic prompt sequences
\e]133;A\a — prompt start
\e]133;B\a — command start
\e]133;C\a — output start
\e]133;D;exitcode\a — command finished
OSC 0/1/2 (title): Window/icon title
Ship integration scripts for bash, zsh, fish in $XDG_DATA_HOME/chiterm/shell-integration/.

4.13 Status Bar
qml

// TerminalStatusBar.qml
Item {
    height: 24
    color: ChiTheme.colors.surfaceContainer

    Row {
        anchors.fill: parent
        anchors.margins: 4
        spacing: 12

        // Left: CWD
        IconLabel {
            icon: "folder"
            text: activeSession.currentDirectory
            font: ChiTheme.typography.labelSmall
            color: ChiTheme.colors.onSurfaceVariant
        }

        // Left: Git branch (if available)
        IconLabel {
            visible: activeSession.gitBranch !== ""
            icon: "account_tree"
            text: activeSession.gitBranch
            font: ChiTheme.typography.labelSmall
            color: ChiTheme.colors.onSurfaceVariant
        }

        Item { Layout.fillWidth: true }  // spacer

        // Right: Last command duration
        IconLabel {
            visible: activeSession.lastCommandDuration > 0
            icon: "timer"
            text: formatDuration(activeSession.lastCommandDuration)
            font: ChiTheme.typography.labelSmall
            color: ChiTheme.colors.onSurfaceVariant
        }

        // Right: Last exit code
        Icon {
            source: activeSession.lastExitCode === 0
                    ? "check_circle" : "error"
            color: activeSession.lastExitCode === 0
                   ? ChiTheme.colors.primary
                   : ChiTheme.colors.error
            size: 14
        }
    }
}
