4.15 Tier 1 — Acceptance Criteria
 Can launch default shell and interact normally
 All common TUI apps work: vim, neovim, tmux, htop, lazygit, btop
 Passes vttest basic suite
 True color test (awk 256-color gradient) renders correctly
 Tabs: create, close, switch, reorder
 Splits: create H/V, navigate, close, maximize
 Search: find text, regex, navigate matches
 Copy/paste works correctly (including bracketed paste)
 Context menu appears with correct items
 Config file loads and applies correctly
 Hot reload of colors/fonts works
 Font zoom works
 Scrollback works (mouse wheel + Shift+PageUp/Down)
 Shell integration shows CWD, timing, exit codes
 Startup time < 100ms to first rendered frame
 cat large file throughput > 500 MB/s
 No visible tearing in Neovim with fast scrolling
5. Tier 2 — Power Features
Goal: Features that elevate Chi Terminal from "good terminal" to "can't go back to anything else." Session management, productivity tools, and desktop integration.

