14. Chi-Specific UI Architecture
Here's how the terminal maps to your Chi components:

qml

ChiApplicationWindow {
    // No TopAppBar — terminal maximizes screen real estate
    // Tab bar IS the top bar
    
    Column {
        // Tab Bar (custom thin component)
        TerminalTabBar { /* tabs + new tab + menu */ }
        
        // Main content area
        TerminalPaneContainer {
            // Recursive split tree
            TerminalPane { /* VTE widget */ }
        }
        
        // Optional: Status bar at bottom
        TerminalStatusBar { /* CWD, git branch, time */ }
    }
    
    // Overlays
    CommandPalette { /* Ctrl+Shift+P */ }
    SearchOverlay { /* Ctrl+Shift+F */ }
    
    // Side panels (slide in)
    SideSheet { /* AI Assistant */ }
    SideSheet { /* Settings */ }
    SideSheet { /* SSH Manager */ }
}
Key Chi Components Used:
Tabs → Terminal tab bar
Menu/ContextMenu → Right-click menus
TextField → Search bar, command palette input
Card → Settings panels, AI chat bubbles
IconButton → Toolbar actions
SideSheet → AI panel, settings
Dialog → Confirmations, connection dialogs
Snackbar → Notifications ("Command completed")
Chip → Tags for sessions, SSH bookmarks
Switch → Settings toggles
Slider → Opacity, font size
SegmentedButton → Layout selector
SearchBar → Command palette
15. What NOT to Build (Anti-Patterns)
23
 Contrary to any "modern" interfaces, a terminal is fast and responsive. There are no animations or other superfluous visual baggage.
❌ Heavy animations on terminal content (Chi motion tokens are for UI chrome only)
❌ Mandatory cloud accounts
❌ Electron/web-tech rendering for the terminal grid
❌ Arbitrary splitter dragging (use smart layouts instead)
❌ Feature overload at launch — progressive disclosure
❌ Built-in file editor trying to compete with vim/nano (just preview)
❌ Custom shell — always use the user's shell
16. Summary: Design Pillars
Fast by default — GPU-rendered grid, instant startup, no lag
Zero-config beauty — Chi Material 3 theming out of the box
Block-based intelligence — Commands are first-class objects
Keyboard-sovereign — Everything accessible without mouse
Context-aware menus — Right-click shows relevant actions
Smart layouts, not splitters — Predefined + zen-mode toggle
AI-ready, privacy-first — Local models first, cloud optional
Session durability — Never lose your workspace
Desktop citizen — Notifications, quake-mode, file drag
Progressive disclosure — Simple surface, deep power underneath
This gives us a terminal that's as clean as Ghostty, as smart as Warp, as flexible as Wave, and as beautiful as nothing else — because it's the only one built on Material 3 Expressive design tokens.

Shall I proceed to the actual implementation architecture and start building the QML components?





I want us to buuild a modern qml based terminal using my qml based ui library (# Chi UI Library - LLM Context File

This file provides comprehensive context for AI assistants working with the Chi UI library.

Overview
Chi is a Material 3 Expressive UI library for Qt/QML applications targeting Unix-based desktop systems. It provides production-ready components with automatic theme management, accessibility support, and desktop-optimized sizing.

Import Statement:

qml

import Chi 1.0
Architecture
Core Design Philosophy
Desktop-first: Components use desktop-optimized sizes and interaction patterns
Zero-configuration: Import and use - sensible defaults for 90% of use cases
Theme-driven: All colors, typography, and motion use ChiTheme tokens
Dieter Rams principles: Less but better - no unnecessary complexity
Theme System
Chi uses a singleton ChiTheme that provides:

qml

ChiTheme {
    // Theme state (synced with C++ backend)
    property bool isDarkMode: true
    property color primaryColor: "#673AB7"  // seed color
    
    // Functions
    function setDarkMode(dark)
    function setPrimaryColor(color)
    function toggleDarkMode()
    
    // Color tokens (Material 3)
    property var colors: {
        primary, onPrimary, primaryContainer, onPrimaryContainer,
        secondary, onSecondary, secondaryContainer, onSecondaryContainer,
        tertiary, onTertiary, tertiaryContainer, onTertiaryContainer,
        error, onError, errorContainer, onErrorContainer,
        background, onBackground, surface, onSurface,
        surfaceVariant, onSurfaceVariant,
        surfaceContainerLowest, surfaceContainerLow, surfaceContainer,
        surfaceContainerHigh, surfaceContainerHighest,
        outline, outlineVariant, shadow, scrim, surfaceTint,
        inverseSurface, inverseOnSurface, inversePrimary
    }
    
    // Typography tokens
    property var typography: {
        displayLarge:   { family, size: 57, weight: 400, spacing: -0.25, lineHeight: 64 },
        displayMedium:  { family, size: 45, weight: 400, spacing: 0,     lineHeight: 52 },
        displaySmall:   { family, size: 36, weight: 400, spacing: 0,     lineHeight: 44 },
        headlineLarge:  { family, size: 32, weight: 400, spacing: 0,     lineHeight: 40 },
        headlineMedium: { family, size: 28, weight: 400, spacing: 0,     lineHeight: 36 },
        headlineSmall:  { family, size: 24, weight: 400, spacing: 0,     lineHeight: 32 },
        titleLarge:     { family, size: 22, weight: 400, spacing: 0,     lineHeight: 28 },
        titleMedium:    { family, size: 16, weight: 500, spacing: 0.15,  lineHeight: 24 },
        titleSmall:     { family, size: 14, weight: 500, spacing: 0.1,   lineHeight: 20 },
        bodyLarge:      { family, size: 16, weight: 400, spacing: 0.5,   lineHeight: 24 },
        bodyMedium:     { family, size: 14, weight: 400, spacing: 0.25,  lineHeight: 20 },
        bodySmall:      { family, size: 12, weight: 400, spacing: 0.4,   lineHeight: 16 },
        labelLarge:     { family, size: 14, weight: 500, spacing: 0.1,   lineHeight: 20 },
        labelMedium:    { family, size: 12, weight: 500, spacing: 0.5,   lineHeight: 16 },
        labelSmall:     { family, size: 11, weight: 500, spacing: 0.5,   lineHeight: 16 }
    }
    
    // Motion tokens
    property var motion: {
        durationFast: 100,
        durationMedium: 250,
        durationSlow: 350,
        durationExpressive: 600,
        easeStandard: Easing.OutCubic,
        easeEmphasized: Easing.OutQuart
    }
}
