└── README.md
Dependencies
Qt 6.5+
Qt Quick
Qt Quick Controls (Basic style)
Qt Quick Effects (MultiEffect for shadows)
Qt Quick Shapes (CircularProgressIndicator)
Best Practices
Always use ChiTheme tokens - Never hardcode colors or sizes
Semantic variants - Use variant names that describe intent, not appearance
Size consistency - Use consistent size scales across components in the same UI
State handling - Let components manage their own visual states
Accessibility - Components include A11y support; don't override
Performance - Components use layer.enabled sparingly for effects
Common Mistakes to Avoid
Wrong import: Use import Chi 1.0 NOT import SmartUIBeta
Hardcoded colors: Use ChiTheme.colors.primary instead of "#673AB7"
Ignoring theme sync: Use ChiTheme functions to change theme, not direct property assignment
Size mismatches: Keep button sizes consistent within button groups) i want you to make thorough research on a feature set of a modern terminal app, what makes them tick, to the most smallest details, what do normal users want, how helpful should they be, modern features like context menus, tabs, panes, how do we minimize the need for things like splitters and unnecessary bloat, a powerful minimal terminal but yet so powerful. what are the core modern features and the rise of ai tools, and modern tui requirements, desktop intergrations and much more
